  lines:
  - entity: 2
    text: Dear you were very generous to the shepherd yesterday.
  - entity: 1
    text: I'm a king after all. I have to take care of my vassals. However, he only
      asked for 10 gold so he could enlarge his farm.
  - entity: 2
    text: King Argorn III would never do that. You know how greedy he is.
  - entity: 0
    text: Knock knock knock. (Door knocked)
  - entity: 2
    text: Who can it be at such an early hour?
  - entity: 1
    text: Definitely the royal harlequin again. I told you not to give him the wine...
  - entity: 0
    text: (The door opened)
  - entity: 3
    text: Your Highness. The village of Northyard was raided at night. Most people
      escaped but some died. We couldn't ...
  - entity: 1
    text: Wait what happened. Talk more slowly. Can't you see I just woke up?
  - entity: 3
    text: The guard informed me that unknown monsters had appeared. Literally monsters.
      They ravaged the whole village.
  - entity: 1
    text: Monsters? Such is written only in ancient books. Hmmm
  - entity: 1
    text: If only the magician Rewind was here. He would know best what could be
      behind it.
  - entity: 3
    text: Your Highness, what should I do? They will be in front of the walls at
      any moment. Northyard is unfortunately the nearest village.
  - entity: 1
    text: Call the crossbowmen to prepare a crossbow tower. We will defend ourselves
      from a distance. Whatever it is we have to fight!
